  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>radishes </strong>in half</p><p>Cut a large sheet of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of a sheet of A3 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>chopped radishes</strong>,<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and<strong> feta cheese </strong>in the middle of the tin foil and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Make 2 parcels and use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1600695388366-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1600695388366-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1600695388366-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1600695388366-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1600695388366-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> honey</strong> and <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> to a small bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Whisk it together with a fork – this is your <strong>honey balsamic</strong> <strong>marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604424629524-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604424629524-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604424629524-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604424629524-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604424629524-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drizzle the <strong>honey balsamic</strong> <strong>marinade </strong>all over the <strong>feta</strong>,<strong> radishes</strong> and<strong> Tenderstem</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the tin foil together to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until everything is cooked and tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1600695413066-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1600695413066-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1600695413066-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1600695413066-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1600695413066-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse the <strong>quinoa</strong> in a sieve under<strong> cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with a matching lid with 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1600695438299-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1600695438299-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1600695438299-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1600695438299-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1600695438299-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail then peel lengths off the<strong> courgette </strong>until you end up with a pile of courgette 'ribbons'</p><p>Wash the <strong>baby kale</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Once the quinoa is cooked, add the<strong> quinoa</strong> and <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>baby kale</strong> and add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give it a gentle mix up (clean hands is the best way!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
